                            <comment id="71668" author="di.wang" created="Fri, 15 Nov 2013 20:00:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;duplicate with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4223&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity test_32c, test_32d: could not find any free loop device&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4223&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4223&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="71667" author="di.wang" created="Fri, 15 Nov 2013 19:59:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CMD: wtm-17vm3 test -b ldiskfs&lt;br/&gt;
wtm-17vm3, /dev/lvm-Role_MDS/P1, /mnt/mds1, -o loop&lt;br/&gt;
CMD: wtm-17vm3 mount -t ldiskfs -o loop /dev/lvm-Role_MDS/P1 /mnt/mds1&lt;br/&gt;
wtm-17vm3: mount: could not find any free loop device&lt;br/&gt;
CMD: wtm-17vm3 mkdir /mnt/mds1/OBJECTS&lt;br/&gt;
CMD: wtm-17vm3 cp /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/admin_quotafile_v2.usr /mnt/mds1/OBJECTS&lt;br/&gt;
CMD: wtm-17vm3 cp /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/admin_quotafile_v2.grp /mnt/mds1/OBJECTS&lt;br/&gt;
CMD: wtm-17vm3 umount -f /mnt/mds1&lt;br/&gt;
wtm-17vm3: umount2: Invalid argument&lt;br/&gt;
wtm-17vm3: umount: /mnt/mds1: not mounted&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems loop device is leaking, so this should be related with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4223&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity test_32c, test_32d: could not find any free loop device&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4223&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4223&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
